Phi_Fi here, and I'm only mentioning this because I think who I am is relevant for providing an example.
I think both charts can be broken down onto four categories for personal ranking.

>Consumption: How actively do you seek out furry media to consume.
>Production: How much furry media do you produce.

And each of those are subdivided with a focus on Internalizing vs. Externalizing.

>Internalized Consumption: you take in furry media increasingly as a way of defining yourself.
>Externalized Consumption: you take in furry media to increasing degrees of exclusivity as an interest.
>Internalized Production: you produce content that increasingly becomes an act of self expression
>Externalized Production: you produce content that increasingly becomes about defining a world or exploring concepts

These are actually four separate dimensions so you can't do a political compass like chart. A 0-4 scale could be used for each of the four categories to map nicely to the existing chart. A normie would be 0 in all categories. A total degenerate furfag would be a 4 in all categories, every aspect of their life revolves around "furriness". This also recognizes that their is not a clear divisor between furry and furfag, its mostly a distinction onto whether you are externally or internally focused.

This is where I feel I am personally:

IC: 2
>I keep personal and fur related social media segregated. But where appropriate I do a lot of theory crafting and speculation.
EC: 3
>I consume a lot of online furry content but largely don't care about tv shows or movies. Lots of media interest outside of furdom.
IP: 0
>I abhor fursonas and the like, my self definition is not influenced by furry media at all.
EP: 4
>Obviously I'm doing a lot of furry centered writing.

Thanks for attending my TED talk.
